    <main class="main">
        <section class="hero">
            <h1>Common Questions</h1>
        </section>

        <section class="app-segment dark">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>What is SSH?</h2>
                <p class="app-description">SSH (Secure Shell) is a protocol for securely connecting to remote servers. It encrypts communication, allowing you to run commands on another machine safely.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="app-segment light">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>What is a host and which port should I use?</h2>
                <p class="app-description">The host is the IP address or domain name of your server. The default SSH port is 22, but many administrators change it for security. If you're unsure, check with your server administrator.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="app-segment dark">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>What are shell commands?</h2>
                <p class="app-description">Shell commands are text-based instructions you run in the terminal to interact with your server, such as `ls` to list files or `docker ps` to show running Docker containers.</p>
                <img src="/images/containeye-framed/in-terminal-with-suggestions.png" alt="Terminal with command suggestions" class="showcase-img">
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="app-segment light">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>What is a regular expression (regex)?</h2>
                <p class="app-description">A regular expression is a pattern used to match text. In ContainEye, regex is used in test validations to ensure the output of a command is what you expect.</p>
                <img src="/images/containeye-framed/test-details-adapt-this-test-command-last-run-expected-output-last-output.png" alt="Test validation with regex" class="showcase-img">
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="app-segment dark">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>How do I delete a server or test?</h2>
                <p class="app-description">Long-press on a server or test in the list and select "Delete" from the context menu.</p>
                <img src="/images/containeye-framed/test-detail-title-dropdownmenu-edit-delete.png" alt="Delete option in dropdown menu" class="showcase-img">
            </div>
        </section>
